FELIX UKA, SAMPSON NWAFOR ABAKALIKI  – The Chairman, All Pro­gressives Congress (APC), Ebonyi State, Chief Stanley Okoro Emegha has applaud­ed Governor David Umahi for declaring his intention to run for the office of the president of Nigeria in the forthcoming general elections in 2023. He briefed newsmen in Abakaliki, Ebonyi state cap­ital barely 24 hours after Governor Umahi formally informed President Muham­madu Buhari of his desire to succeed him in office at Asorock Villa, State House, Abuja. NYSC Gets Commendation On Innovative Service Delivery Absence of Governing Council Hindering AAU Progress, ASUU… At the party’s secretariat in Abakakili Chief Okoro Emegha described Umahi’s intention to run as a bold step, noted that he is confi­dent that Umahi’s presiden­cy will bring massive infra­structural development and economic prosperity to the Nigerian Nation and her cit­izenry considering his monu­mental achievements both in his private life and as Ebonyi state governor “Let me inform Nigerians both at home and in the dias­pora that Governor Umahi’s decision to join the presiden­tial race is the best thing that has happened to the entire country, Nigeria consider­ing his precedence and gene­alogy. Just like what he said on the Channels TV where he promised to replicate his Progressive efforts in Ebonyi at the National level. My Gov­ernor is not contesting with total obedience to the party’s decision”.